      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make the lye solution",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Gloves and goggles on. Add the sodium hydroxide to the distilled water slowly and stir until dissolved. Allow to cool to 38-42°C.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Prepare the oils and blend",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Melt the coconut oil if solid. Combine all oils and allow to reach 38-42°C. Pour the lye solution into the oils in a slow stream. Stick-blend in 5-second bursts to ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "trace",
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termId": "cmpba33kq0009v8v4r8ss8v4h"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": ". The ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "saponification",
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termId": "cmpba33i60005v8v4c5e638ns"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": " moves at a comparable pace to a standard olive-coconut recipe. At light trace, add the rose geranium essential oil and blend for 10 seconds. Pour into the mould immediately.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Mould and cure",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Insulate and leave 24-48 hours. Wear gloves to unmould and cut. Cure on an open rack for 4-6 weeks. The ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "superfat",
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termId": "cmpba33jh0007v8v49iaitckh"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": " fraction from the sweet almond oil gives a softer, more emollient feel than an all-olive bar.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Storage and shelf life",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Keep bars on an open rack in a cool, dark place. The higher linoleic acid content from the sweet almond oil means the shelf life is 18 months rather than the 2 years of a pure olive bar. Check for DOS (orange spots) and a paint-like rancidity smell at 12 months. Discard any bar showing either sign. Label the bar with the tree nut content if gifting.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
